West Nile fever, Italy
----------------------
Information received on (and dated) 15 Sep 2011 from Prof Dr Romano
Marabelli, Chief Veterinary Officer, Department for Veterinary Public
Health, Nutrition and Food Safety, Ministry of Health, Rome, Italy

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 22 Aug 2011
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 13 Sep 2011
Report date: 15 Sep 2011
Date submitted to OIE: 15 Sep 2011
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: October 2009
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: West Nile virus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (WNF 1) Sesto al Reghena, Pordenone, Friuli-Venezia Giulia
Date of start of the outbreak: 22 Aug 2011
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals
Species: Equidae
Susceptible: 11
Cases: 1
Deaths: 0
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0
Affected population: the positivity regards a sentinel horse detected
in the framework of the national surveillance plan.

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or
inconclusive; vectors

Control measures
Measures applied: no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals.
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Experimental Zooprophylactic Institute
(IZS), Teramo (national laboratory)
Species: Equidae
Test: IgM-capture ELISA
Test date: 13 Sep 2011
Result: positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

