West Nile fever, Spain
----------------------
Information received on (and dated) 12 Sep 2011 from Dr Lucio Ignacio
Carbajo Goni, [Deputy Director General of Animal Health, General
Directorate of Agricultural and Livestock Resources, Ministry of
Environment and Rural and Marine Affairs], Madrid, Spain

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 3 Sep 2011
Date of 1st confirmation of the event: 8 Sep 2011
Report date: 12 Sep 2011
Date submitted to OIE: 12 Sep 2011
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 28 Oct 2010
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: West Nile virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (1/2011) Barbate, La Janda, Cadiz, Andalusia
Date of start of the outbreak: 3 Sep 2011
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Species: Equidae
Susceptible: 31
Cases: 1
Deaths: 0
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or
inconclusive; vectors

Control measures
Measures applied: control of arthropods, no vaccination, treatment of
affected animals (non-steroidal anti-inflammatories. Vitamin B.)
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Central Veterinary Laboratory, Algete
(national laboratory)
Species: Equidae
Test: IgM-capture ELISA
Test date: 8 Sep 2011
Result: positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

